com.net2plan.utils

Class Triple<A,B,C>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.net2plan.utils.Triple<A,B,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - Class type for the first element
    B - Class type for the second element
    C - Class type for the third element

    public class Triple<A,B,C>
extends Object

    A tuple consisting of three elements. There is no restriction on the type of the objects that may be stored.

    Example:

    Map&lt;String, Object&gt; map = new LinkedHashMap&lt;&gt;();
    map.put("parameter", "value");
    Integer number = new Integer(3);
    String string = "Test";

    Triple&lt;Map&lt;String, Object&gt;, Integer, String&gt; data = new Triple&lt;&gt;(map, number, string);

    ...

    Map&lt;String, Object&gt; myMap = data.getFirst();
    Integer myNumber = data.getSecond();
    String myString = data.getThird();
    Author:
    Pablo Pavon-Marino, Jose-Luis Izquierdo-Zaragoza
    See Also:
    Pair, Quadruple, Quintuple
